President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring May 1, 2014, as Law Day, U.S.A. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of the right to vote and the need to protect it. It acknowledges the struggles that many Americans went through to secure the right to vote and calls for continued efforts to eliminate barriers to voting. The proclamation also mentions a bipartisan commission's recommendations for reforms to protect the right to vote and urges states and local election officials to implement these recommendations. Additionally, it calls on Congress to update the Voting Rights Act. The proclamation encourages Americans to recognize the importance of the nation's legal and judicial systems and to display the flag in support of Law Day.